{"id":"math120-vareval2-fg001","cid":"MATH 120","topic":"Functions and Graphs","subtopic":"Evaluating functions","difficulty":1,"license":"CC BY-NC-SA (Numberbender original)","instruction":"A profit function is P(x) = {a}x^2 + {b}. Find P({x_val}).","params":{"a":{"type":"int","min":-4,"max":-1},"b":{"type":"int","min":50,"max":200},"x_val":{"type":"int","min":2,"max":6}},"answer_expr":"vareval2","steps":["Substitute x = {x_val}: P({x_val}) = {a}({x_val})^2 + {b}.","= {a}({x2}) + {b} = {ax2} + {b} = {answer_vareval2}."],"tags":["survey-calculus","functions","quadratic","business"]}
